17 (2) A description of the risk factors and warning signs associated with sickle cell disease;
18 (3) A recommendation to the parent or guardian of those students displaying warning
19 signs associated with sickle cell disease that such parent or guardian consult with the
20 student's primary care provider to determine if immediate screening for sickle cell disease
21 is appropriate;
22 (4) A description of the screening processes for sickle cell disease; and
23 (5) A recommendation that, following a sickle cell disease diagnosis, the parent or
24 guardian consult with the student's primary care provider to develop an appropriate
25 treatment plan.
26 (b) The Department of Education, in cooperation with the Department of Public Health,
27 shall develop and make available the information about sickle cell disease to local school
28 systems as required under subsection (a) of this Code section in an efficient manner that
29 shall include posting the information on its public website."
30 SECTION 2.
31 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
